text:
You and your team hosted a wonderful conference Katie Lee Koven

Katie Lee Koven is with Julie Margueritte Taquin and Zaira Arredondo.
12 hrs ·

A few pics from the Association of Academic Museums and Galleries conference. Darren Parry gave an incredible opening keynote. We had excursions to various places, one to Golden Spike and Spiral Jetty. It was great to spend some time with colleagues. Alexandra did an amazing job managing logistics for this hybrid conference. There were both in person and virtual presenters and attendees. It was kind of amazing that we pulled it off! Thanks to my staff as well who gave a lot of their time to do things they don’t typically have to do- like be tech support for a virtual session. They are so awesome.

text:
Whew! The last few days were amazing. Mormon History Association Conference in Logan. I was blessed to lead a Pre-conference tour with my friend Paul Willie and learn about Willie handcart company and where he settled. We went to the old Washakie Townsite and then to the baptismal site of my people on the Bear River. A quick stop in Wellsville to learn about Black Pioneer slaves and ended the tour in Hyrum with Jaime Huss.

Friday morning I gave the opening Plenary and followed that up with a panel on “Women and Historical Agency” with two wonderful women who I admire so much, Brooke LeFevre and Katie Ludlow Rich. I also received 2 awards🙏

So many friends and so many wonderful papers and memories. Logan Utah and Utah State University you did not disappoint.
#MHAM2022 #MHARochesterNY
#UntilWeMeetAgain
#IAmTired
